properties.description:
Actual donuts! 8 small donuts cooked fresh in the oil with sugar on top. Just like home.

Golden Donut
Urfahraner-Herbstmarkt 
4040 Linz

The Doughnut Plant
220 W 23rd St
New York, NY

I had an expensive Vanilla Bean (glazed raised) doughnut, $4, which was not fluffy but chewy. No normal chocolate donuts either.

Alpha Donuts
45-16 Queens Blvd
Sunnyside, NY

Nice donut diner.

The Donut Pub
203 W 14th St
New York, NY

I had a Whole Wheat (plain old fashioned) and a Chocolate Ring (glazed raised). $4.50

Peter Pan Donut & Pastry Shop
727 Manhattan Ave
Brooklyn, NY

I had a chocolate French crueler. Tasted great. Two donuts, two coffees, $4.50 -- what a deal!

Moe's Doughs
126 Nassau Ave
Brooklyn, NY

I had a chocolate raised. Best donut yet!

Rosedale Donuts
2681 Calloway Dr # 308
Bakersfield, CA 

Cheap and tasty donuts! Chocolate raised was good, the old-fashioned okay. Worth a visit should you find yourself at this shopping strip in Bakersfield.

Yummy's Donut House
7625 W Hampden Ave
Lakewood, CO

Hippie Mermaid Donut Co
150 Palomino Trail
Ridgway, CO

If you ever want a donut and an empanada served by bona fide hippies this is the joint for you.

Brothers Coffee & Donuts
2063 Larimer St
Denver, CO

I had a chocolate old fashioned, a raised, and an espresso. I expected hipster donuts but they were solid and cheap.

LaMar's Donuts
133 McCaslin Blvd
Louisville, CO 80027

It's a small chain (maybe 30 locations in 4 states) so I'll let it slide... good donuts and coffee.

Daylight Donuts 
1410 North Ave
Grand Junction, CO

It's a big chain but $3 for two donuts and a coffee! Good donuts, good deal.
